<div class="slide">
	<h1>1993</h1>
	<h2>The Web almost died at birth.</h2>
	<p class="huge center"><code>&lt;img src="" /&gt;</code></p>

	<ul class="citations">
	<li><a href="http://diveintomark.org/archives/2009/11/02/why-do-we-have-an-img-element">diveintomark.org/archives</a></li>
	</ul>
</div>

<div class="slide">
	<h1>1993</h1>
	<p><img class="left" src="../img/presentations/Mosaic_browser_plaque_ncsa.jpg" alt="Mosaic web browser placard." title="" /></p>
	<p class="big center">This is where Al Gore comes in.</p>
  <p class="incremental">
  The funding for Marc's web browser project at U of Illinois came from the
  High Performance Computing and Communication Act of 1991, one of several
  computing developments initiated by <span class="highlight">U.S. Senator Al Gore</span>.
  </p>

	<ul class="citations">
	<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mosaic_%28web_browser%29">Wikipedia Mosaic Web Browser</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mosaic_browser_plaque_ncsa.jpg">photo credit</a></li>
	</ul>
</div>

<div class="slide">
	<h1>1995</h1>
	<h2>The infamous bubble.</h2>
	<p><img class="left" width="50%"src="../img/presentations/NASDAQ_IXIC_-_dot-com_bubble_small.png" alt="The dot com bubble chart." title="" /></p>
	<p>Netscape was founded in 1994 by Marc Andreesen.</p>
	<p>The Navigator browser was released on November 14th, 1994.</p>
	<p>Netscape went public in 1995</p>

	<ul class="citations">
	<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Netscape">Wikipedia Netscape</a></li>
