<div class="slide">
	<h1>2010</h1>
	<h2>The landscape has shifted.</h2>
	<table>
	<thead>
		<tr><th>Store</th><th>App Count</th><th>Users</th></tr>
	</thead>
	<tbody>
			<tr><td>App Store (Apple)</td><td>300,000</td><td>120 million</td></tr>
			<tr><td>Android Market (Google)</td><td>156,000</td><td>13 million</td></tr>
			<tr><td>App World (BlackBerry)</td><td>9,808</td><td>46 million</td></tr>
			<tr><td>Ovi Store (Nokia)</td><td>6,118</td><td>250 million</td></tr>
			<tr><td>App Catalog (Palm/HP)</td><td>5,184</td><td>2.6 million</td></tr>
	</tbody>
	</table>

	<ul class="citations">
	<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_digital_distribution_platforms_for_mobile_devices">Wikipedia Distribution platforms</a></li>
	</ul>
</div>

<div class="slide">
	<h1>2010 continued</h1>
	<h2>The Internet is <em>not</em> the Web.</h2>
    <p>The Web is just one Internet <em>application</em> out of many.</p>
    <p>Facebook, Twitter, Foursquare, Google Docs, Salesforce.com, Zimbra, etc.
        are spilling over from the web onto the Internet.</p>
</div>

<div class="slide">
	<h1>Act III</h1>
	<p class="big center">This is all out war for Internet 2.0.</p>
	<p class="center">Will it be open, or controlled by gatekeepers?</p>
</div>

<div class="slide">
	<h1>The nukes are pointed.</h1>
	<p class="center">The space race was not about controlling space, but
	<em>preventing anyone else</em> from controlling it alone.</p>
</div>

<div class="slide">
	<h1>It is <em>not</em> a zero-sum game.</h1>
	<p class="center">No browser holds a majority of mind share this time.</p>
