<div class="slide">
	<h1>Give them a reason to compete.</h1>
    <h2>Our window of opportunity:</h2>
	<p class="center">If we don't start building awesome apps in the next generation web browsers; our
	opportunity will be lost forever.</p>
</div>

<div class="slide">
	<h1>The JavaScript renaissance.</h1>
	<h2>A diamond is emerging from the rough.</h2>
	<p class="left"><a href='https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/RegExp' title='JS RegExp .constructor'><img src='http://static.jsconf.us/promotejsh.gif' height='150' width='180' alt='JS RegExp .constructor'/></a></p>
	<h4>Some things you should know:</h4>
	<ul class="right">
	<li>Java is to Javascript what car is to carpet.</li>
	<li>Oracle now owns the trademark; so we'll call it JS from now on.</li>
	<li>JS is the most widely deployed programming environment in the World.</li>
	<li>JS got fast at some point along the way.</li>
	<li>Full stack JS is now possible (client, server, and database).</li>
	</ul>

	<ul class="citations">
	<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ECMAScript">Wikipedia ECMAScript</a></li>
	</ul>
</div>

